    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup today is anchored by three high-upside plays that capitalize on favorable matchups and situational advantages. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.22) commands the highest score of the day, buoyed by a strong BvP history and a favorable matchup against Bello. He is closely followed by **Kyle Tucker** (76.90) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.68), both of whom benefit from positive wind conditions and projected platoon advantages. **Josh Lowe** (72.20) also presents significant value; beyond his solid matchup against Fedde, his score received a unique boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a high-probability opportunity for him to pad our scarce stolen base totals.\n\nWhile the core of the lineup is set, the decision to bench **Miguel Vargas** (58.56) was the most difficult pivot of the day. Despite a solid score driven by a favorable batting order position, **Miguel Vargas** was pushed out by the higher efficiency of **Marcell Ozuna** and the overall depth of the infield/utility corps. Elsewhere, we are navigating a few situational hurdles: **Drake Baldwin** faces the toughest matchup of the day against the elite Skubal, suppressing his output, while the rainout of **Gunnar Henderson** and the lingering injury to **Jordan Westburg** leave us shuffling depth behind **Nasim Nunez** and **Jacob Wilson** to maintain production in the middle infield. We will continue to monitor the status of bench assets like **Brady House**, **Heliot Ramos**, and **Coby Mayo** as we look to conserve game caps for later in the week.",
